Author-Name: Jianjun Miao  
Author-Name: Pengfei Wang  
Title: Bubbles and Total Factor Productivity 
Abstract:
 This paper presents an infinite-horizon model of production economies in
 which firms face idiosyncratic productivity shocks and are subject to
 endogenous credit constraints. Credit-driven stock price bubbles can arise
 which can relax credit constraints and reallocate capital more efficiently
 among firms. The collapse of bubbles causes a fall of total factor
 productivity.
