Author-Name: Felix Kubler  
Author-Name: Karl Schmedders  
Title: Financial Innovation and Asset Price Volatility 
Abstract:
 We compare asset prices in an overlapping generations model for incomplete
 and complete markets. Individuals within a generational cohort have
 heterogeneous beliefs about future states of the economy and thus would
 like to make bets against each other. In the incomplete-markets economy,
 agents cannot make such bets. Asset price volatility is very small. The
 situation changes dramatically when markets are completed through
 financial innovations as the set of available securities now allows agents
 with different beliefs to place bets against each other. Wealth shifts
 across agents and generations. Such changes in the wealth distribution
 lead to substantial asset price volatility.
