Title: International Robust Disagreement 
Abstract:
 We characterize the equilibrium of a two-country, two-good economy in
 which agents have opposite preference bias toward one of the two
 consumption goods and fear model misspecification. We document that
 disagreement about endowments' growth prospects is a persistent endogenous
 outcome of this class of economies.
