Author-Name: Olivier Jeanne  
Title: Capital Flow Management 
Abstract:
 There is a wide variety in the capital account policies of emerging
 markets and developing economies. Some countries, such as Brazil, have
 recently experimented with prudential controls on capital inflows, whereas
 others, such as China, have continued to maintain tight controls. This
 paper reviews the recent theoretical literature explaining the motivations
 behind capital account policies, and whether there is a case for
 international coordination in this area.
