Author-Name: Robert L. Clark  
Author-Name: Melinda Sandler Morrill  
Author-Name: Steven G. Allen  
Title: Effectiveness of Employer-Provided Financial Information: Hiring to Retiring 
Abstract:
 Workers plan and save for retirement throughout their careers. Individuals
 must navigate complex financial instruments and understand public and
 employer-provided retirement plan characteristics. Beginning when a worker
 is first hired, most employers provide the option to contribute to
 retirement saving plans. As workers near retirement, they face many
 choices that have considerable consequences for their retirement income
 security.  At these two important periods, employers can provide timely
 information assisting workers in making choices that optimize lifetime
 wellbeing. Our research, conducted in cooperation with several large
 employers, illustrates the importance of employer-provided education in
 increasing worker understanding of several retirement-related issues.
