Author-Name: Jason D. Hartline  
Title: Approximation in Mechanism Design 
Abstract:
 This paper considers three challenge areas for mechanism design and
 describes the role approximation plays in resolving them. Challenge 1:
 optimal mechanisms are finely tuned to precise details of the distribution
 on agent preferences.	Challenge 2: in environments with multi-dimensional
 agent preferences economic analysis has failed to provide general
 characterizations optimal mechanisms. Challenge 3: optimal mechanisms are
 parameterized by unrealistic knowledge of the distribution of agents'
 private preferences.  This paper surveys positive resolutions to these
 challenges with emphasis on basic techniques and their relevance to theory
 and practice.
