Author-Name: Paul L. Joskow  
Author-Name: Catherine D. Wolfram  
Title: Dynamic Pricing of Electricity 
Abstract:
 As both a regulator and an academic, Fred Kahn argued that end-use
 electricity consumers should face prices that reflect the time-varying
 marginal costs of generating electricity. This has been very slow to
 happen in the US, even in light of recent technological advances that have
 lowered costs and improved functionality for meters and automated demand
 response technologies. We describe these recent developments and discuss
 the remaining barriers to the proliferation of time-varying electricity
 pricing.
