Author-Name: Jonathan Vogel  
Author-Name: Su Wang  
Title: Global Supply Chains and Wage Inequality 
Abstract:
 A salient feature of globalization in recent decades is the emergence of
 "global supply chains" in which different countries specialize in
 different stages of a sequential production process. In Costinot, Vogel
 and Wang (2011) (CVW hereafter), we have developed a simple theory of
 trade with sequential production to shed light on how global supply chains
 affect the interdependence of nations. In this paper we develop a
 multi-factor extension of CVW to explore how the emergence of global
 supply chains may affect wage inequality within countries. 
