Author-Name: Ralph Ossa  
Title: Profits in the "New Trade" Approach to Trade Negotiations 
Abstract:
 I highlight two advantages of adopting a "new trade" approach to trade
 negotiations. First, it allows for a view of trade negotiations in which
 producer interests play a prominent role. And second, it lends itself
 naturally to quantitative analyses of non-cooperative and cooperative
 trade policy. My specific focus is on profit shifting effects through
 which countries can gain at the expense of one another.
