Author-Name: Frank Schorfheide  
Author-Name: Kenneth I. Wolpin  
Title: On the Use of Holdout Samples for Model Selection 
Abstract:
 Researchers often hold out data from the estimation of econometric models
 to use for external validation. However, the use of holdout samples is
 suboptimal from a Bayesian perspective, which prescribes using the entire
 sample to form posterior model weights. This paper examines a possible
 rationale for the use of holdout samples: data-inspired modifications of
 structural models are likely to lead to an exaggeration of model fit. The
 use of holdout samples can, in principle, set an incentive for the modeler
 not to exaggerate model fit.
