Author-Name: Martin B. Hackmann  
Author-Name: Jonathan T. Kolstad  
Author-Name: Amanda E. Kowalski  
Title: Health Reform, Health Insurance, and Selection: Estimating Selection into Health Insurance Using the Massachusetts Health Reform 
Abstract:
 We implement an empirical test for selection into health insurance using
 changes in coverage induced by the introduction of mandated health
 insurance in Massachusetts. Our test examines changes in the cost of the
 newly insured relative to those who were insured prior to the reform. We
 find that counties with larger increases in insurance coverage over the
 reform period face the smallest increase in average hospital costs for the
 insured population, consistent with adverse selection into insurance
 before the reform. Additional results, incorporating cross-state variation
 and data on health measures, provide further evidence for adverse
 selection. 
