Author-Name: Sarah Miller  
Title: The Impact of the Massachusetts Health Care Reform on Health Care Use among Children 
Abstract:
 In 2006 Massachusetts enacted a major health care reform aimed at
 achieving near-universal coverage in the state. While other studies have
 found that this reform substantially affected the use of health services
 in general, the impact of the reform on children is largely unexplored.
 Children are of special interest to policymakers because it is widely
 believed that better health in early childhood results in large payoffs to
 adult health and achievement. I analyze how the reform affected the
 insurance coverage, health care utilization patterns, and health outcomes
 of children under 18 years old.
