Author-Name: John A. Graves  
Author-Name: Jonathan Gruber  
Title: How Did Health Care Reform in Massachusetts Impact Insurance Premiums? 
Abstract:
 It is widely recognized that the 2006 Massachusetts health reforms served
 as a blueprint for national reform under the 2010 Affordable Care Act
 (ACA).  As such, there is interest in using the Massachusetts experience
 to understand how insurance premiums might change under the ACA.  In this
 paper, we analyze changes in private insurance premiums in Massachusetts
 between 2002 and 2010.  In contrast to earlier estimates from
 Massachusetts (Cogan, Hubbard and Kessler 2010), we find no statistical
 evidence of changes in group premiums.  By contrast, we find large
 reductions in non-group premiums in Massachusetts relative to the rest of
 the U.S.  
