Author-Name: James A. Freeman  
Author-Name: Akwasi Nti-Addae  
Title: Access to Credit by Small Businesses: How Relevant Are Race, Ethnicity, and Gender? 
Abstract:
 This paper employs data from the 1998 and 2003 Survey of Small Business
 Finances to analyze whether, after controlling for observable factors that
 influence loan decisions, there is a significant difference in the loan
 approval rate and the interest rate charged on approved loans for
 businesses owned by minority or white females and firms owned by white
 males.
