Author-Name: Henry Hyatt  
Author-Name: Erika McEntarfer  
Title: Job-to-Job Flows in the Great Recession 
Abstract:
 We develop prototype job-to-job flow measures to provide new evidence on
 labor turnover and earnings dynamics in the Great Recession. We find a
 sharp drop in job mobility in the Great Recession, much sharper than the
 previous recession, and higher earnings penalties for job transitions with
 an intervening nonemployment spell. Focusing on residential construction
 separators in particular, we find increasing rates of industry change and
 higher earnings penalties from job change in the Great Recession.
